text: National Highway 965DD, commonly referred to as NH 965DD is a national highway in India. It is a secondary route of primary National Highway 65. NH-965DD runs in the state of Maharashtra in India. == Route == NH965DD connects Lonand, Andori, Shirwal, Bhor, Apti, Mahad, Mandangarh and Pacharal in the state of Maharashtra. == Junctions == : Terminal near Lonand. : near Shirwal : near Mahad == See also == * List of National Highways in India * List of National Highways in India by state == References == == External links == * NH 965DD on OpenStreetMap Category:National highways in India Category:National Highways in Maharashtra
